The paper discusses the design of spectrum sharing algorithms in cognitive radio networks using game theoretic analysis and behavioral economic theory. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also considers the impact of human decision making on pricing and management of radio resources, which could fall under the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a new pricing mechanism for improving radio resource management, which could also fall under the Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-category. However, given the focus on cognitive radio networks and spectrum sharing, cs.CR is the most likely sub-category.
